{"id": "EUVD-2026-2509", "enisaUuid": "478aafb3-d2dd-3a85-9fb5-5bdbbb87b3f6", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfs: PM: Fix reverse check in filesystems_freeze_callback()\n\nThe freeze_all_ptr check in filesystems_freeze_callback() introduced by\ncommit a3f8f8662771 (\"power: always freeze efivarfs\") is reverse which\nquite confusingly causes all file systems to be frozen when\nfilesystem_freeze_enabled is false.\n\nOn my systems it causes the WARN_ON_ONCE() in __set_task_frozen() to\ntrigger, most likely due to an attempt to freeze a file system that is\nnot ready for that.\n\nAdd a logical negation to the check in question to reverse it as\nappropriate.", "datePublished": "2026-01-14T15:05:55", "dateUpdated": "2026-01-14T15:05:55", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-71106", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/222047f68e8565c558728f792f6fef152a1d4d51", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b107196729ff6b9d6cde0a71f49c1243def43328"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-71106", "GHSA-65w6-rwf9-587r"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1e109f6e-e05a-3d2d-ac5f-f5ebc87dd15e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18.3"}, {"id": "28f24e37-5565-3ce3-b930-2d8e6a34cdde", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "a3f8f8662771285511ae26c4c8d3ba1cd22159b9 <b107196729ff6b9d6cde0a71f49c1243def43328"}, {"id": "60cc7dcf-4764-36cc-80c6-93b3e2b6dd63", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "a3f8f8662771285511ae26c4c8d3ba1cd22159b9 <222047f68e8565c558728f792f6fef152a1d4d51"}, {"id": "7a84156d-b0d1-3ba9-9798-8c6ea07fb5f1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.18"}, {"id": "d7fbd0a7-74e1-385b-8aac-c3896578a1d2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.19-rc1"}, {"id": "e4ca1a3f-1be6-3202-940b-0808c7d34eb4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "c6914e0e-149e-328b-a